Joe:
My dog is an Alsatian bitch.

23
00:02:55,185 --> 00:02:57,449
Her name is Tulip.

24
00:02:57,487 --> 00:03:00,354
I've never owned a dog
before her.

25
00:03:00,390 --> 00:03:03,553
Alsatians have a bad reputation.

26
00:03:03,594 --> 00:03:06,495
They are said to bite the hand
that feeds them.

27
00:03:06,530 --> 00:03:10,967
Indeed, Tulip bit my hand once,
but accidentally.

28
00:03:11,001 --> 00:03:12,628
She mistook it
for a rotten apple

29
00:03:12,669 --> 00:03:15,194
we were both trying to grab
simultaneously.

30
00:03:15,239 --> 00:03:19,642
One of her canines sank
into my thumb joint to the bone.

31
00:03:19,676 --> 00:03:21,166
Oh, well.
We... we all make mistakes.

32
00:03:21,211 --> 00:03:24,078
 
And she was dreadfully sorry.

33
00:03:24,114 --> 00:03:26,674
She rolled over
with all her legs in the air,

34
00:03:26,717 --> 00:03:30,016
and, later on, when she saw
the bandage on my hand,

35
00:03:30,053 --> 00:03:31,520
she put herself in the corner,

36
00:03:31,555 --> 00:03:33,580
the darkest corner
of the bedroom,

37
00:03:33,624 --> 00:03:35,819
and stayed there
for the rest of the afternoon.

38
00:03:35,859 --> 00:03:38,350
She could hardly do more
by way of apology,

39
00:03:38,395 --> 00:03:41,057
for she'd become
so hysterically excited

40
00:03:41,098 --> 00:03:43,623
at the mere hint
of being taken out for a walk

41
00:03:43,667 --> 00:03:46,693
that she rushes into the kitchen
to grab the vegetables

42
00:03:46,737 --> 00:03:49,035
and scatters them
all about the corridor

43
00:03:49,072 --> 00:03:50,903
as if they were rose petals,

44
00:03:50,941 --> 00:03:54,672
marking her ascension
to heaven.

45
00:03:54,711 --> 00:03:59,512
It seems to me
both touching and strange

46
00:03:59,549 --> 00:04:02,780
that she should find the world
so wonderful.

47
00:04:02,819 --> 00:04:06,118
 

48
